summary: Any of the GoT ships, bc I ship all three and 11. :D thank you darling!!
question: Any of the GoT ships, bc I ship all three and 11. :D thank you darling!!
answer:
11. Fireplace

Pairing:  Arya Stark/Gendry Waters | Baratheon

Gendry shivered, and Arya knew that because his teeth clacked together and his entire body drew tightly into the chair. He shifted, tucking the fur more snugly around his shoulders.

Rubbing his hands together, he blew on them, creating quite the spectacle, if Arya was in the mood for something to spectate.

Which she wasn’t.

“Would you like another fur, your excellency?” she quipped, lounging back in her own chair as he attempted to scoot his own closer to the roaring fireplace.

Gendry glared in her direction. “I’m not used to this freezing cold weather.”

Arya chuckled and rose from her chair. “So that’s a yes to another fur?”

He smirked and reached for her, pulling her into his lap. “Yes, I think this one will do nicely…”

body:
#downwithkimilia

Usually I stay out of ship wars but when you bring the ACTORS AS IN REAL LIFE PEOPLE into them that’s when I get involved.

People have photshopped Emilia over the RoseKit wedding pictures and their honeymoon pictures with dumb captions like:

“can’t wait for Emilia to leak the affair ”

or

“Emilia and Kit are totally doing it in Rose’s bed.”

Let me get ONE THING CLEAR!!!!

Emilia Has stated MULTIPLE TIMES that she would never date and has never dated Kit Harington she said

“there’s an image of kit and I kissing in our "Rolling Stone.” Issue back in 2011, that kiss was staged by the photographer as Kit And Rose had already been together for six months at that point.“

She then stated:

"I’m not interested in dating actors, I tried it and it didn’t work, I appreciate people wanting me to be happy, but I will choose who with.”

Please don’t be disrespectful and disgusting enough to photshop precious and memorable images. You wanna ship the disgusting cesspool Jon*rys fine but LEAVE KIT AND EMILIA OUT OF IT!!!!!

Thank you for coming to my ted talk.

body:
joytblue replied to your post “hufflepuffdisaster replied to your post “Are we sure Arya is a real…”

@silencefromafar Do you think we will see Arya’s language skills? In the book I heard she can speak High Valyrian, which would be so cool if the show Arya surprises Daenerys by speaking high Valyrian

Idk dear. I didn’t know about Arya speaking high valyrian, I haven’t got there yet with reading asoiaf. I’m more interested in seeing which role Arya will play in the war against the Others with her assassin skills tbh. Arya is a fighter but she’s not a warrior like Jon or Brienne. I mean her abilities are more on the one-on-one combat and stealth and infiltration side, where language skills are very useful. And I want to see how the writers plan on using these :)
